# Managing Xen Hosts

## Get help about xl command

    xl help

## List all active systems

    sudo xl list

## Start guest system

    sudo xl create /etc/xen/<domU>.cfg

## Connect to running Guest

    sudo xl console <domU>

## Shutdown a guest

    sudo xl shutdown <domU>

## Remove a guest

    sudo lv remove /dev/xen-vg/<disk-name>         -- do it for each LVM disk

    sudo rm /etc/xen/<domU>.cfg                    -- ATTENTION maybe youwant to keep teh config file...